KGs are also used in a plethora of downstream tasks, and social biases engraved in KG embeddings get propagated [Groth2022KnowledgeGA, Kraft2022TheLO]. Specifically, ontology creation, which generally comprises manual rules factored by opinions, motivations, and personal choices, is a source of bias [Janowicz2018DebiasingKG, Du2022UnderstandingGB]. Also, automated pipelines for KG construction exhibit gender bias [Mehrabi2019ManIT]. There are other similar concerns of LLMs beyond bias and fairness, including (but not limited to) copyright violation and misinformation. In general, due to the implicit nature of parametric knowledge, it is less straight forward to forget such toxic information from LLMs, compared to explicit knowledge.